    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p><code>clean</code> is its own build lifecycle phase (which can be thought of as an action or task) in Maven. <code>mvn clean install</code> tells Maven to do the <code>clean</code> phase in each module before running the <code>install</code> phase for each module.</p>\n\n<p>What this does is clear any compiled files you have, making sure that you're really compiling each module from scratch.</p>\n"
