    "question_id" : 6018701,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can call more than one <strike>target</strike> goal with maven. <code>mvn clean install</code> calls <code>clean</code> first, then <code>install</code>. You have to clean manually, because clean is not a standard <strike>target</strike> goal and not executed automatically on every install.</p>\n\n<p><code>clean</code> removes the target folder - it deletes all class files, the java docs, the jars, reports and so on. If you don't <code>clean</code>, then maven will only \"do what has to be done\", like it won't compile classes when the corresponding source files haven't changed (in brief).</p>\n\n<p><sup>we call it <em>target</em> in ant and <em>goal</em> in maven</sup></p>\n"
  }, {
